{
  "texts": [
    "'Decentralized Governance,' encompassing community-driven research and decentralized decision-making principles, was referenced by 20.5% of experts.",
    "'Organizational Structure,' referring to participation by nonaffiliated individuals and DeSci organizations like DAOs, was cited by 17.9% of respondents.",
    "These aspects reflect a shift towards more inclusive and participatory governance models in scientific research.",
    "The 'Innovative Aspects' category consolidates viewpoints on the novel and transformative potential of DeSci, referenced by 28.2% of experts.",
    "This category focuses on the evolution of existing scientific models and the creation and sharing of intellectual property."
  ]
}